description.narrative:
Core-support is provided to LRCM for 2018-2021 to develop internal capacities to manage results, monitoring and reporting skills and to contribute to the promotion of accountable justice and CSOs in Moldova. According to the RAF, 2 main objectives are to be supported as following:

1. consolidated rule of law and democracy in Moldova as a result of this objective: 
- judges would be appointed and promoted in a transparent and merit-based manner;
- judges would be more independent, impartial and accountable;
- judiciary is effectively organized and managed;
- human rights in Moldova are better respected;
- CSOs are strengthened to effectively and freely engaged in public polices and assist/engage citizens.

2. LRCM would be a sustainable NGO and an organizational role model for other CSOs from Moldova. This objective will be managed through the following interventions:
1. LRCM would be managed efficiently;
2. LRCM communication, visibility and advocacy skills would be improved;
3. LRCM staff would be professional and united;
4. Financial, environmental sustainability and conflict sensitivity would be improved;
5. LRCM is adequately equipped and its cyber security is at high level.
